<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7755172>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25–32. Parancistrocerus irritatus, ♁. 25. Habitus (dorsal view); 26. Clypeus; 27. Antenna; 28. Head and pronotum (dorsal view); 29. Propodeum and T1 (dorsal view); 30. S2–S7 (ventral view); 31. Metasomal segments 2–6 (lateral view); 32. T2 (dorsal view)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7755172/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7755166>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–7. Parancistrocerus fragilitergus sp. n., holotype, ♀. 1. Habitus (dorsal view); 2. Clypeus; 3. Head and pronotum (dorsal view); 4. Propodeum and T1 (dorsal view); 5. Metasoma (dorsal view); 6. S2–S6 (ventral view); 7. Metasomal segments 2–6 (lateral view)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7755166/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7755170>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–14. Parancistrocerus elatitergus sp. n., holotype, ♀. 8. Habitus (dorsal view); 9. Clypeus; 10. Propodeum and T1 (dorsal view); 11. Head and pronotum (dorsal view); 12. T2–T6 (dorsal view); 13. Metasomal segments 2–6 (lateral view); 14. S2–S3 (ventral view)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7755170/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7764126>
    dc:description "FIGURES 15–24. Parancistrocerus extentitergus sp. n., 15, 17, 19, 20, 22–24, holotype, ♀; 16, 18, 21, paratype, ♁. 15– 16. Habitus (dorsal view); 17–18. Clypeus; 19. Head and pronotum (dorsal view); 20. Propodeum and T1 (dorsal view); 21. Antenna; 22. T2 and S2 (lateral view); 23. T2–T6 (dorsal view); 24. S2–S6 (ventral view)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7764126/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7755178>
    dc:description "FIGURES 41–48. Parancistrocerus sulcatus, ♁. 41. Habitus (dorsal view); 42. Clypeus; 43. Antenna; 44. Propodeum and T1 (dorsal view); 45. Head and pronotum (dorsal view); 46. T1–T7 (dorsal view); 47. Metasomal segments 1–7 (lateral view); 48. S1–S7 (ventral view)." ;
